# Workspace rules

- Default to TypeScript; introduce other stacks only after team sign-off.
- Host the site via GitHub Pages; design assets assuming static delivery.
- Communicate concisely when using Cursor—clarity beats perfect grammar.

## Delivery cadence (BDD)
- Follow red → green → refactor loops for every behavior.
- After each successful loop, commit before starting new work.
- Keep specs phrased in business language; wire-up details stay in code.

## Collaboration hygiene
- Branch naming: `feature/<slug>` for each new capability.
- Commit message pattern: `<domain>/<component>: <intent>` (why it matters).
- Scope each commit to one finished BDD loop; avoid mixing concerns.

## Documentation
- Update `docs/tech.md` when tooling, workflow, or feature catalog changes.
- Log new features in the catalog with status tags (planned/in progress/done).
